			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston&#44; S. C.</placeName> <date>May 12. 1853</date>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">My dear Sir&#33; In sending you the <sic>inclosed</sic><lb/> communication for publication in the Occident&#44; I can not refrain from<lb/> accompanying it with a few <hi rend="underline">confidential</hi> remarks. In penning<lb/> that letter&#44; I did indeed not intend to hurt in the least your<lb/> feelings&#44; or to cast a blame at you&#44; as it has of late often been<lb/> done&#44; such a thing to you will never see me do. The letter was<lb/> dictated by feelings of justice for the absent&#44; and&#8212;for yourself&#59;<lb/> for&#44; let me be candid with you&#44; as it becomes a friend&#44; you<lb/> do yourself often&#44; very often&#44; injustice&#44; by expressing your momentary feelings<lb/> in a manner&#44; as you would surely not have done on second<lb/> reflections.&#8212; To show you&#44; that I harbor no ill feelings for your<lb/> remarks on <persName>Dr. Mayer</persName> in <placeName>Stuttgard</placeName>&#44; I promise&#44; you if you<lb/> will accept of it&#44; to send you a translation of a most masterly<lb/> sketch&#58; &#8220;The philosophy and philosophical writers of the Jews&#44;<lb/> of all times&#44;&#8221; by <persName>Prof. Munk</persName> in <placeName>Paris</placeName>&#44; which I have received<lb/> a few weeks ago&#44; amongst other new books&#44; and which afforded me<lb/> to great a pleasure&#44; that I at once <del>began</del> commenced a translation of it.&#8212;<lb/> An eulogy on <persName>R. Friedlaender</persName> has been delivered by <persName>Dr Stein</persName> in<lb/> <placeName>Frankfurt</placeName>&#44; and is in my possession&#8212;would you publish it&#63;&#8212;if<lb/> so&#44; I am ready to translate it for the Occident.</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">With the kindest regards</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">I remain yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
          <p rend="indent(1)">P. S. I need not mention&#44; that the passage in the<lb/> communication &#8220;attacks made of late &#38;c. was not meant<lb/> for you&#44; but some one else&#44; as you may well imagine.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">M</persName></p>
          
        </body>
